<div class="kksr-legend" style="font-size: 19.2px;">
            5/5 - (1 vote)    </div>
    </div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Normally people travel to<a href="https://asuaire.com/en/visit-costa-rica/destinations"> Costa Rica </a>during Dry Season where everything&#8217;s sunny and pretty much alive, but it can get to be a little too much for some travellers. </span><b>Once you get to</b><b> enjoy this country with a little bit of rain, you&#8217;ll discover its charm and won’t want Green Season to end!</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Here <a href="https://asuaire.com/en">Asuaire Travel Agency </a>shares with you eight true reasons why <strong>Green Season is secretly the best time to visit Costa Rica</strong>:</span></p>
<div id="toc_container" class="toc_light_blue no_bullets"><p class="toc_title">Contenido</p><ul class="toc_list"><li></li><li><ul><li></li></ul></li><li><ul><li></li></ul></li><li></li><li></li><li></li><li></li><li><ul><li></li></ul></li></ul></div>
<h2><span id="1_Lush_rainforest_grows_intensely"><b> 1. Lush rainforest grows intensely</b></span></h2>
<p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-17321 size-full_content" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20960%20640'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="rainforest" width="960" height="640" title="Green Season" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/rainforest.png 960w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/rainforest-600x400.png 600w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/rainforest-300x200.png 300w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/rainforest-768x512.png 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/rainforest-960x640.png" /><noscript><img class="aligncenter wp-image-17321 size-full_content" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/rainforest-960x640.png" alt="rainforest" width="960" height="640" title="Green Season" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/rainforest.png 960w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/rainforest-600x400.png 600w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/rainforest-300x200.png 300w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/rainforest-768x512.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You’ve never truly experienced such vibrant and intense vegetation until you <strong>visit Costa Rica’s rainforests during <a href="https://asuaire.com/blog/trip-guide/three-reasons-travel-costa-rica-rainy-season?lang=en">Rainy Season</a></strong>!</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">It tends to rain almost every afternoon, so thanks to this, plants absorb much more water and grow in a real obvious way all over the country. <strong>You’ll even find vegetation growing in between concrete in the streets. </strong>It’s beautiful!</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The weather becomes cooler than dry season which is nicer for people who are not loving real heavy warm weather. Perfect for <strong><a href="https://asuaire.com/en/costarica/tours/nature-en/monteverde-cloud-forest-reserve-hike">hiking through the lush rainforest</a>!</strong></span></p>
<h2><span id="2_Summer_shines_in_the_Caribbean"><strong>2. Summer shines in the Caribbean</strong></span></h2>
<p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-17322 size-full_content" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20960%20640'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="puerto-viejo-beach" width="960" height="640" title="Green Season" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/puerto-viejo-beach.png 960w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/puerto-viejo-beach-600x400.png 600w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/puerto-viejo-beach-300x200.png 300w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/puerto-viejo-beach-768x512.png 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/puerto-viejo-beach-960x640.png" /><noscript><img class="aligncenter wp-image-17322 size-full_content" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/puerto-viejo-beach-960x640.png" alt="puerto-viejo-beach" width="960" height="640" title="Green Season" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/puerto-viejo-beach.png 960w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/puerto-viejo-beach-600x400.png 600w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/puerto-viejo-beach-300x200.png 300w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/puerto-viejo-beach-768x512.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">There’s a real <strong>interesting fact about Costa Rica’s weather</strong>. Did you know that you can be in the city of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_Jos%C3%A9,_Costa_Rica" target="_blank" rel="noopener">San José </a>enjoying a regular sunny day, but then, if you drive down 20 minutes towards the <a href="https://asuaire.com/en/costarica/packages/most-popular/costa-rica-caribbean-pacific-11-days">Caribbean</a> you’ll find a total opposite weather? <strong>Cloudy forest with enormous green leaves hanging over the road</strong>, like in <a href="https://asuaire.com/en/costarica/tours/nature-en/braulio-carillo-rain-forest-aerial-tram-tour">Parque Nacional Braulio Carrillo</a>.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Basically, when it starts raining all around the country it’s probably sunny in the <a href="https://asuaire.com/blog/trip-guide/vacations-caribbean-costa-rica?lang=en">South Caribbean Coast</a>. Interesting, right?</span></p>
<h3><span id="Find_out_more_about_vacations_in_Costa_Rica8217s_Caribbean_Coast_here"><a href="https://asuaire.com/blog/trip-guide/vacations-caribbean-costa-rica?lang=en">Find out more about vacations in Costa Rica&#8217;s Caribbean Coast here.</a></span></h3>
<h2><span id="3_More_luxury_for_less"><strong>3. More luxury for less</strong></span></h2>
<p><img class="alignnone wp-image-17323 size-full_content" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20960%20640'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="bungalow-in-rainforest" width="960" height="640" title="Green Season" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/bungalow-in-rainforest.png 960w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/bungalow-in-rainforest-600x400.png 600w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/bungalow-in-rainforest-300x200.png 300w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/bungalow-in-rainforest-768x512.png 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/bungalow-in-rainforest-960x640.png" /><noscript><img class="alignnone wp-image-17323 size-full_content" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/bungalow-in-rainforest-960x640.png" alt="bungalow-in-rainforest" width="960" height="640" title="Green Season" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/bungalow-in-rainforest.png 960w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/bungalow-in-rainforest-600x400.png 600w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/bungalow-in-rainforest-300x200.png 300w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/bungalow-in-rainforest-768x512.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Between the months of <strong>May and November Low Season begins</strong>, where about every tour and hotel reduce their rates. You’ll find a lot more specials and availability during this season!</span></p>
<h3><span id="Design_the_ideal_low_budget_luxury_trip_for_you_here"><a href="https://asuaire.com/en/costarica/packages/honeymoon/experience-nature-and-luxury-at-the-beach"><strong>Design the ideal low budget luxury trip for you here.</strong></a></span></h3>
<h2><span id="4_Uncrowded_popular_destinations">4. Uncrowded popular destinations</span></h2>
<p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-17324 size-full_content" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20960%20640'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="traveller-hanging-bridge" width="960" height="640" title="Green Season" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/traveller-hanging-bridge.png 960w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/traveller-hanging-bridge-600x400.png 600w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/traveller-hanging-bridge-300x200.png 300w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/traveller-hanging-bridge-768x512.png 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/traveller-hanging-bridge-960x640.png" /><noscript><img class="aligncenter wp-image-17324 size-full_content" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/traveller-hanging-bridge-960x640.png" alt="traveller-hanging-bridge" width="960" height="640" title="Green Season" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/traveller-hanging-bridge.png 960w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/traveller-hanging-bridge-600x400.png 600w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/traveller-hanging-bridge-300x200.png 300w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/traveller-hanging-bridge-768x512.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">High Season can actually become a real busy time for tourism in Costa Rica. Traffic increases and beaches get real crowded. As for <strong>Green Season</strong>, you’ll easily find parks, trails or even beaches all to yourself to enjoy. <strong>The quieter the place is, the more of nature you’ll get to admire!</strong></span></p>
<p><a href="https://asuaire.com/blog/trip-guide/top-5-undiscovered-spots-in-costa-rica-that-will-take-your-breath-away?lang=en">Discover five <strong>undiscovered spots in Costa Rica</strong> here that will take your breath away.</a></p>
<h2><span id="5_Amazing_animal_migration_begins">5. Amazing animal migration begins</span></h2>
<p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-17325 size-full_content" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20960%20640'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="humpback-whale" width="960" height="640" title="Green Season" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/humpback-whale.png 960w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/humpback-whale-600x400.png 600w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/humpback-whale-300x200.png 300w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/humpback-whale-768x512.png 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/humpback-whale-960x640.png" /><noscript><img class="aligncenter wp-image-17325 size-full_content" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/humpback-whale-960x640.png" alt="humpback-whale" width="960" height="640" title="Green Season" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/humpback-whale.png 960w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/humpback-whale-600x400.png 600w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/humpback-whale-300x200.png 300w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/humpback-whale-768x512.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px" /></noscript></p>
<p>It&#8217;s that time of the year where all kinds of <strong>animals migrate to Costa Rica</strong>. From immense <a href="https://asuaire.com/blog/trip-guide/whales-dolphins-watching-costa-rica?lang=en"><strong>humpback whales</strong></a> splashing to <a href="https://asuaire.com/blog/en/costa-rica"><strong>turtles nesting</strong></a> in the South Pacific Coast. It&#8217;s a wonderful time to visit the area of <strong><a href="https://asuaire.com/en/costarica/packages/honeymoon/costa-rica-with-corcovado-13-days">Osa Peninsula</a> for a true wildlife experience</strong>!</p>
<p><a href="https://asuaire.com/blog/trip-guide/the-top-10-exotic-animals-in-costa-rica?lang=en">Learn which are 10 most <strong>exotic animals to see in Costa Rica</strong> here.</a></p>
<h2><span id="6_Coffee_harvest_season_is_here"><strong>6. Coffee harvest season is here!</strong></span></h2>
<p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-17326 size-full_content" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20960%20640'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="coffee-production" width="960" height="640" title="Green Season" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/coffee-production.png 960w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/coffee-production-600x400.png 600w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/coffee-production-300x200.png 300w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/coffee-production-768x512.png 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/coffee-production-960x640.png" /><noscript><img class="aligncenter wp-image-17326 size-full_content" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/coffee-production-960x640.png" alt="coffee-production" width="960" height="640" title="Green Season" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/coffee-production.png 960w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/coffee-production-600x400.png 600w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/coffee-production-300x200.png 300w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/coffee-production-768x512.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px" /></noscript></p>
<p>For many coffee lovers this can sound like heaven! How about experiencing <a href="https://asuaire.com/en/costarica/tours/nature-en/poas-volcano-doka-grecia-sarchi"><strong>picking and making real fresh Costa Rican coffee</strong></a>? And learn a lot more about the history and culture its <strong>coffee production.</strong></p>
<h2><span id="7_Immensewaterfalls_flowing"><strong>7. Immense waterfalls flowing</strong></span></h2>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-21822" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20960%20640'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="waterfalls flowing" width="960" height="640" title="Green Season" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/waterfalls-flowing.png 960w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/waterfalls-flowing-510x340.png 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/waterfalls-flowing-900x600.png 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/waterfalls-flowing-768x512.png 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/waterfalls-flowing-600x400.png 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/waterfalls-flowing.png" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-21822" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/waterfalls-flowing.png" alt="waterfalls flowing" width="960" height="640" title="Green Season" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/waterfalls-flowing.png 960w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/waterfalls-flowing-510x340.png 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/waterfalls-flowing-900x600.png 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/waterfalls-flowing-768x512.png 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/waterfalls-flowing-600x400.png 600w" sizes="(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px" /></noscript></p>
<p>Since it rains a lot more, rivers are fuller. Which make <strong>waterfalls spectacular</strong> and the best time to practice the most <a href="https://asuaire.com/en/costarica/tours/adventure/rapidos-rio-pacuare"><strong>exciting white water rafting</strong></a>!</p>
<h2><span id="8_Cozy_rainy_afternoons_to_relax_and_enjoy_the_sounds_of_nature"><strong>8. Cozy rainy afternoons to relax and enjoy the sounds of nature</strong></span></h2>
<p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-17328 size-full_content" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20960%20640'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="hammock-costa-rica" width="960" height="640" title="Green Season" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/hammock-costa-rica.png 960w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/hammock-costa-rica-600x400.png 600w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/hammock-costa-rica-300x200.png 300w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/hammock-costa-rica-768x512.png 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/hammock-costa-rica-960x640.png" /><noscript><img class="aligncenter wp-image-17328 size-full_content" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/hammock-costa-rica-960x640.png" alt="hammock-costa-rica" width="960" height="640" title="Green Season" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/hammock-costa-rica.png 960w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/hammock-costa-rica-600x400.png 600w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/hammock-costa-rica-300x200.png 300w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/hammock-costa-rica-768x512.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px" /></noscript></p>
<p>There&#8217;s nothing as good as travelling and <strong>enjoying the simple pleasures of life</strong>. Something as simple but yet calming, is to sit outside your porch with your <strong>Costa Rican homemade cup of coffee,</strong> and just lay back and enjoy nature&#8217;s Rainy Season show! This is what we call: <strong>Pura Vida</strong>!</p>
<h3><span id="Start_planning_your_next_trip_to_Central_America_with_Asuaire_Travel_Agency_and_enjoy_the_perks_of_Green_Season_in_Costa_Rica_Design_your_customised_trip_now_here"><em>Start planning your next trip to Central America with <a href="https://asuaire.com/en/">Asuaire Travel Agency</a> and enjoy <strong>the perks of Green Season in Costa Rica</strong>! <a href="https://asuaire.com/en/design-your-trip">Design your customised trip now here.</a></em></span></h3>
		</div>

